org.mvp4j.annotation
Annotation Type Model

@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Documented
public @interface Model

The scope of this annotation is the view

Use this to annotate the input component and bind it to the property name of the model The value seized on the input component value will automatically stored in the value of associated property model Example :

Required Element Summary
 java.lang.String property
           
 
Optional Element Summary
 java.lang.String initProperty
           
 

Element Detail

property

public abstract java.lang.String property
Returns:
The property name of the model, that used by component

initProperty

public abstract java.lang.String initProperty
Returns:
The initialization property name of the model, that used by component that needs data to be displayed at rendering. for example a comboBox
Default:
""
